Its amazing how both games are still the peak of open-world game design and yet when you get down to it their design philosophy couldn't be more different.

Now that both are in the hands of the public, I think comparing Elden Ring to Botw is really fun and interesting. Both games refined and expanded upon the open-world genre and are heralded as masterpieces, and yet they take wildly different approaches to do so.
